==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Achilles tendon]]

===Etymology===
A [[calgue]] of {{NL.}} {{term|Achillis tendo|lang=la}}, a term devised by the Dutch anatomist [[w:Philip Verheyden|Philip Verheyden]] in 1693 in reference to the mythological account of [[Achilles]] being held by the heel when dipped in the [[w:Styx|River Styx]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[Achilles]]’ [[tendon]]}}

# {{anatomy}} The strong [[tendon]] formed of the united tendons of the large [[muscle]]s in the [[calf]] of the leg, an inserted into the bone of the heel.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|anatomy}} [[calcaneal tendon]], [[tendo Achillis]], [[tendo calcaneus]]

